== Strategy ==
{{Tile markers box|Module:Tile markers/Waterbirth_Dungeon.json|showpreview=false}}
As the Kings all attack with different styles, reducing the amount of time spent attacking multiple Kings is essential for staying alive and extending trips. This can be done by killing the Kings in a cycle and utilising the downtime before they respawn to safely kill the other kings, by [[Safespot|safespotting]], or by attacking a King outside the aggression range of the others. 

Download the tile markers above to show safespots for [[Dagannoth Rex|Rex]], along with ladder locations throughout the entire dungeon route. 

==== Entering the Lair ====
Upon entering the lair, the player can be targeted by any amount of Kings at the same time, though it is most common to be attacked by both Prime and/or Supreme upon dropping down. [[Protect from Magic]] should be activated '''before''' entering their lair since Prime is likely to be very accurate and also hits the hardest of the three by far.

For players wishing to safespot Rex or Prime, they should enter and exit the room (leaving via the ladder will nullify some incoming attacks if done quickly enough), until they can safely run along the southern side of the island without being targeted by [[Dagannoth Supreme|Supreme]] or [[Dagannoth Prime|Prime]]. Once on the eastern wall, players can attack [[Dagannoth Rex|Rex]] with magic and use either safespot freely.

For players planning on killing all 3 Kings, there are a few common options to start. 

* You can sneak to the eastern wall and start the rotation with '''Rex''' with magic.
* If Supreme is not aggressive, you can run north and begin attacking '''Prime''' with ranged.
* If Prime is not aggressive, you can attempt to kill '''Supreme''' quickly with melee. Note that Supreme's spawn location makes it more likely that a second or third king will notice you, so starting with Supreme is typically the most difficult option.

==== Handling multicombat ====
If multiple Kings begin attacking you, you can attempt to off-tick their attacks and correctly pray against all of them. For a more relaxed approach, you can stick with Protect from Magic while quickly killing Supreme first or safespotting Rex.

With very high defence bonuses (such as with 99 Defence and expensive armour), Rex and Supreme will only have 15-30% accuracy against you. This makes it possible to run in with Protect from Magic and strong melee armour to kill both Supreme and Rex before finally switching to weaker ranged armour to defeat Prime. You will typically take very little damage even if all three kings attack you at once.

==== Tribrid Rotation (3 Kings) ====
Depending on gear and stats, the Kings can be killed quickly enough that there is very little overlap where multiple kings are alive and able to reach the player. Rex can easily be safespotted on the north-eastern, south-eastern, or north-western walls. With a long range ranged weapon, Prime can be reached from the northern side while staying out of the aggression ranges of Supreme and Rex. Supreme, however, should be defeated with melee, and is very close to Prime and Rex. Ideally, defeat Supreme after Prime so both aren't attacking the player at once. 
